Notebook[{
Cell["mma-hol \[Dash] Runnable Examples", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"0aab7d71-ad28-4cb9-8327-a2efadb6c298"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "An LCF-style HOL theorem prover in the Wolfram Language. Evaluate the ",
 "cells top to bottom with Shift+Enter. The first cell loads the prebuilt ",
 "snapshot (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"bootstrap", ".", "mx"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "92d0e7ed-e1c8-4378-8bd6-6cf325faa290"],
 "); if it is missing, run ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"wolframscript", " ", "-", 
   RowBox[{"file", " ", 
    RowBox[{"tests", "/", 
     RowBox[{"build_snapshot", ".", "wls"}]}]}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "133a6770-0c19-4872-963d-e5e7b16b0989"],
 " in the repo root first."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f693bcac-343f-4b6e-89e9-9df4e8adc345"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ee9a85b3-e094-41f1-b331-ad2d3b73e59a"],

Cell["Load the kernel + the full standard library:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"542c9e55-2601-42d8-bae1-f9cbeea15f76"],

Cell["\<\
(* Load the library: Stable mode + restore the prebuilt snapshot. *)
root = ParentDirectory[NotebookDirectory[]];
Global`$HOLEncapsulationMode = \"Stable\";
Get[FileNameJoin[{root, \"bootstrap.mx\"}]];
$ContextPath = Join[
  Select[Contexts[], StringMatchQ[#, \"HOL`*\"] && ! StringContainsQ[#, \
\"Private`\"] &],
  $ContextPath];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"682a8bc4-414b-49d1-b0e4-a837e7de7289"],

Cell["1. The trusted kernel", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"25e4df47-c472-401c-a52c-e9338302a335"],

Cell["\<\
Every value of theorem type is built by the 10 primitive rules. formatThm \
renders a theorem as \[RightTee] p.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0b3ae7b5-b6ef-4cce-a69c-808a29648e45"],

Cell["formatThm[TRUTH]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"45f9831f-b55d-4351-bf09-d58d11482b9f"],

Cell["2. Propositional automation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f9554a7d-e6bf-451b-b29e-e1bd65ad9e25"],

Cell["\<\
propTaut decides propositional tautologies and returns a kernel-checked \
theorem. parseTerm reads HOL syntax (==> implication, \\/ or, ~ not).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"72066a1d-ad1d-41f9-b36f-8964d424e5b9"],

Cell["formatThm[propTaut[parseTerm[\"p ==> p\"]]]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"694ca54d-cac7-41fe-b187-1d5b91139f53"],

Cell["formatThm[propTaut[parseTerm[\"p \\\\/ ~p\"]]]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"98b66e5a-024d-427f-8fa9-a495e5841d94"],

Cell["3. Proving with tactics", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"df9a8108-68a8-41d6-9037-425690520759"],

Cell["\<\
prove[goal, tactic] runs a tactic against a goal and returns the discharged \
theorem.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"288a6f43-9225-4203-98ba-663e8005dd6f"],

Cell["formatThm[prove[parseTerm[\"T\"], acceptTac[TRUTH]]]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"ac76fb80-079d-484e-9ecb-069322771221"],

Cell["4. The standard library: marquee theorems", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"cd6542b3-35fa-4cd1-a041-b87c53e731f5"],

Cell["\<\
The real numbers are built from Dedekind cuts; these are the proven capstones \
of stdlib/Real/ (all 0-sorry, rechecked by the kernel).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"90c93416-0ad5-473e-8a9b-7c1c47de3fe8"],

Cell["\<\
(* Dedekind completeness: every nonempty bounded-above set has a least upper \
bound *)
formatThm[HOL`Stdlib`Real`dedekindCompleteThm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7db84aa6-f786-4d2a-9a3d-a2db72c3e3b5"],

Cell["\<\
(* Bolzano-Weierstrass *)
formatThm[HOL`Stdlib`Real`bwSequentialThm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7167536f-33c9-4aa0-8071-d7a5eed6a84d"],

Cell["\<\
(* Heine-Borel for a closed interval *)
formatThm[HOL`Stdlib`Real`compactnessPrincipleThm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"d6152a25-913c-4ccb-87d2-f1afca831fdd"],

Cell["\<\
(* compact <=> sequentially compact (general real sets) *)
formatThm[HOL`Stdlib`Real`compactIffSequentialCompactThm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"6cc92b81-0eff-4081-b7d8-15da1900c9b9"],

Cell["\<\
(* connected <=> interval *)
formatThm[HOL`Stdlib`Real`connectedIffIntervalSetThm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"768b3d7e-95cb-4b59-9834-0c9cf2500c2b"],

Cell["5. A proof from scratch, checked live", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"cac2063c-704c-443a-b318-a0b0ca347d17"],

Cell["\<\
The cells above only displayed finished theorems. Here we BUILD one: prove \
sets a goal, a tactic discharges it, and the kernel rechecks every step. We \
prove p /\\ q ==> q /\\ p (note the swap).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"38af2790-f742-4534-9977-f61efdc1cea1"],

Cell["\<\
goalA = parseTerm[\"p /\\\\ q ==> q /\\\\ p\"];
thmA = prove[goalA,
  THEN[dischTac,
    THENL[conjTac, {
      acceptTac[CONJUNCT2[ASSUME[goalA[[1, 2]]]]],
      acceptTac[CONJUNCT1[ASSUME[goalA[[1, 2]]]]]}]]];
formatThm[thmA]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"cb88a7dd-271d-4096-8437-ad2cd59a38db"],

Cell["6. Real analysis, proved automatically", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f5416868-5093-4456-aafc-51d65945f31b"],

Cell["\<\
realArithProve decides linear real arithmetic and emits a Farkas certificate \
the kernel replays. A few builders state the goal as a HOL term (we lift the \
forall/imp constants out of parseTerm to avoid typing Unicode), then the \
prover proves the midpoint inequality  a < b ==> a < (a+b)/2  by itself.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0970f50c-71ec-431a-9c82-995d10ce62f1"],

Cell["\<\
realTy = mkType[\"real\", {}];
forallName = parseTerm[\"!z. z\"][[1, 1]];
impName = parseTerm[\"a ==> b\"][[1, 1, 1]];
all[v_, body_] := mkComb[mkConst[forallName, tyFun[tyFun[typeOf[v], boolTy], \
boolTy]], mkAbs[v, body]];
imp[p_, q_] := mkComb[mkComb[mkConst[impName, tyFun[boolTy, tyFun[boolTy, \
boolTy]]], p], q];
nat[n_] := Nest[mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Num`sucConst[], #] &, \
HOL`Stdlib`Num`zeroConst[], n];
rnum[n_] := mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realOfRatConst[], \
mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Rat`ratOfIntConst[], mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Int`intOfNumConst[], \
nat[n]]]];
rLt[u_, v_] := mkComb[mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realLtConst[], u], v];
rAdd[u_, v_] := mkComb[mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realAddConst[], u], v];
rMul[u_, v_] := mkComb[mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realMulConst[], u], v];
rInv[u_] := mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realInvConst[], u];
a = mkVar[\"a\", realTy]; b = mkVar[\"b\", realTy];
midpoint = all[a, all[b, imp[rLt[a, b], rLt[a, rMul[rAdd[a, b], \
rInv[rnum[2]]]]]]];
formatThm[HOL`Auto`RealArith`realArithProve[midpoint]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"57eee628-d795-4ca4-b3df-cac386d4398e"],

Cell["7. \[Dash] and the kernel will not be fooled", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d83bae21-640e-4a92-9e60-70fe0f2b6f85"],

Cell["\<\
The same prover refuses a false statement. Asked to prove  forall x y. x < y  \
it throws rather than return a theorem: that is the LCF trust boundary in \
action.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7df477cf-dc62-4de5-afd1-c6e92e74af91"],

Cell["\<\
x = mkVar[\"x\", realTy]; y = mkVar[\"y\", realTy];
Catch[HOL`Auto`RealArith`realArithProve[all[x, all[y, rLt[x, y]]]], _,
  Function[{v, t}, \"refused: the prover threw rather than return a \
theorem\"]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"cf4e8054-2df7-4000-974a-92a2bd0e5007"],

Cell["Next steps", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"cebc6e82-45ab-4100-b50d-cac24418a489"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "See ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"README", ".", "md"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3ec7c42b-2385-4f4a-9e74-50c43ea7d7fa"],
 " for the project overview and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"docs", "/", 
   RowBox[{"USER_GUIDE", ".", "md"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "484a6f33-0469-4cc3-a0de-166a508812b1"],
 " for the API and how to develop your own proofs."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4110c63d-aa26-4830-a5bf-88c287f77961"]
},
WindowSize->{800, 700},
